Cassiterite, or tin, may be the forgotten battery mineral but it is nonetheless expected to benefit equally from the increase in demand for the product considering it will play a significant role in the lithium-ion battery market. As a result, AIM-listed junior AfriTin is fast tracking the development of its Namibia-based Uis tin mine which, over the course of two phases, will ultimately produce 5 000 tpa of tin concentrate. LAURA CORNISH spoke to AfriTin CEO ANTHONY VILJOEN on the side lines of the 2019 Investing in African Mining Indaba about the company’s strategic vision to become Africa’s tin champion and the steps it will take to achieve this. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 3, 2019 and will be published in full on 3 April 2019 You can read the
full digital magazine here or subscribe here to receive a print copy